						<summary>

						<p>This is a similar gift of 90 sheep for a lamp in the same temple by <hi rend="bold">Bāradāyaṉ Paḷḷi son of Ādanūr-kiḻāṉ</hi> of Ādanūr to be maintained with an <hi rend="italic">uḻakku</hi> of ghee every day by the liquid measure called <hi rend="italic">Tirumaṟaikkāḍaṉ</hi> after the god.</p>						

						</summary>
